WEE Pandimonium <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uleolanhazzan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leolan Hazzan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><FONT COLOR=AA0000><B>Lanys.com Moderator</B></FONT></span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/18/01 12:49:30 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.acinternet.com/leolan/leopic.asp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just something I noticed...</span><hr size=1> I think most low levels just don't know about them. <p>&nbsp;- Leo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukinekoreq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KinekorEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/18/01 1:56:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just something I noticed...</span><hr size=1> I think Leo hit the mark, I myself did not find out about this board until about level 40 or so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usalamren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salamren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/18/01 1:57:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just something I noticed...</span><hr size=1>  Any advice on clericdom? Well that's kind of a general question there young Gnome. <br>
<br>
 Hunting grounds - I'd suggest around the mino cave in Steamfront, or Crushbone. One suggestion, do not try to escape the orcs by jumping in the water! At around your age I learned that orcs can swim quite well. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
 <br>
 Equipment - A very nice hammer can be obtained by slaying Red 5 a rouge clockwork in the mines of malfunction in Ak'Anon. Speak with Manik Compolten in Gemchopper Hall about Red 5. He won't always give you the Bullsmasher though, sometimes patchwork armor, or a wooden shield, or whatever else Manik finds under his desk. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
 Experiment with your stun spell. You will learn to love this level 5 spell. It will serve you well for the rest of your clerical career.<br>
<br>
Salamren Mechamender<br>
Gnomish Templar of Brell <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usalamren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salamren</A> at: 5/18/01 2:00:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udravmere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dravmere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/18/01 2:11:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just something I noticed...</span><hr size=1> Already got my Bullsmasher! &lt;swelling with pride&gt;<br>
<br>
Stun, I haven't used much.  I've worked with root and sooth more. I'll have to work on that.  I know a few orcs that could use a good stunning. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'm right now looking for items that increase Wisdom. I've been told that will help. I've looked on Allakazam, however the items I've seen are either crafted or dropped by rather scary mobs.<br>
<br>
Larbrac<br>
11th Level Cleric of Brell<br>
WEE Pandimonium<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucalbegath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calbegath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/18/01 3:13:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just something I noticed...</span><hr size=1> Hail, fellow wee cleric!<br>
<br>
Salamren is right on:  stun will be powerful to ye for as long as ye serve Brell.  I personally got chewed on quite a bit when soothe failed me, especially as time went on, but many folks say it's great if yer careful with it.  A cleric at yer level also makes a decent wizard, as well.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Some easy and fairly cheap wisdom gear to obtain:<br>
<br>
-- +2 wis rings are available from a jeweler fer only a few plat (3-5pp) each.  If yer still living on Faydwer, there's often a young enchanter or two in Greater Faydark who can make these.  +2 wis earrings require more skill ta make, and are more expensive (20-25pp each).<br>
<br>
-- A black iron medallion (+3 wis, neck) sells fer around 20pp.<br>
<br>
-- A savant's cap (+3 wis, head) is normally 20 or 25pp as well.<br>
<br>
It's a matter of personal opinion, but I find that having good armor is just as important as wisdom gear.  At yer level banded armor will do the job nicely; ye can buy small banded from a blacksmith fer a few plat per piece (1pp/ac is normal pricing).<br>
<br>
Best of luck, and may ye enjoy being a cleric! <p>Cheers,<br>
<br>
<img src="http://members.aol.com/deepgreyocean/calb.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucalbegath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calbegath</A> at: 5/18/01 3:18:11 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utordil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tordil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/18/01 3:54:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just something I noticed...</span><hr size=1> /shrug never used stun.. never found a use for it but that's just IMO. <p><center><b><br>Tordil Tanksaver</b>
