</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uworthyiam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Worthy Iam</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/18/01 6:55:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just something I noticed...</span><hr size=1> Never used STUN?<br>
<br>
/boggle<br>
/faint<br>
<br>
Stun has ALOT of uses. At level 54, I find it is my most often loaded offensive spell.<br>
<br>
Against Caster mobs, it will stop them from getting their spell off. Especially the gating ones who come back with friends.<br>
<br>
Stunning a MOB durring combat with a group means that he is going to not be hitting your group for a few seconds, and, when you get to karnor, that will mean saving yourself a few hundread HP of healing.<br>
<br>
Trying to GATE in a bad situation? Hit your opponent with STUN first, might give you the couple seconds you need.<br>
<br>
If you are a lower level Cleric who Melee's some, an occasional stun keeps the mob from hitting you for a few seconds while you self heal.<br>
